{
  "stem": "33.3",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 233,
      "text": "There was an SS officer above him in rank, who did not live in the camp, nearby somewhere.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 234,
      "text": "He came in every day only for roll call, maybe for 15 minutes or half an hou.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 235,
      "text": "We had a roll call when we came back from the factory.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 236,
      "text": "As far as we knew, he didn't allow physical punishment while he was there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 237,
      "text": "So while he was there, that half an hour or 15 minutes, nobody was beaten.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 238,
      "text": "But we really can thank him for our lives, because he did have standing orders to destroy all of us before our liberation.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 239,
      "text": "Basically, there wasn't any point to it to do it, because we were liberated by the Americans, which compared to being liberated by the Russians, was a much better deal for them.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 240,
      "text": "Two weeks before we were liberated-- I've left Auschwitz with a cousin of mine, who is the younger sister of this cousin who saved my life, and who's closer to my age, but we were separated in Braunschweig.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So she knew where I went, but I didn't know where she went.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I went first.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "About two weeks before liberation, everything was already pretty chaotic.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We could see the Allied airplanes flying over, and-- it's interesting, you know, talking about that.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had air raids practically every night while I was in Salzwedel.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "This was 1945 already.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we knew it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "About five minutes after 8 o'clock, we're going to go down to the shelter, so everybody started to go to the bathroom, like about a quarter to 8.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we, we were in the factory.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At night, we went to the shelter.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But if we were in camp, we didn't have any shelter, of course.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But somehow, I think, most of us weren't afraid.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
